JOHANNESBURG - A memorial service for Karabo Mokoena will be held today at the Diepkloof hall in Soweto.It gets under way at two o'clock in the afternoon.Mokoena's charred body was discovered in Lyndhurst, Johannesburg, a day after she'd been reported missing last month.Results from DNA tests have confirmed that the remains are indeed hers. Her alleged killer Sandile Mantsoe's facing a charge of murder and defeating the ends of justice.Mokoena will be buried at the Westpark Cemetery on Friday.eNCA